The paper discusses a method of sampling using timing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also deals with the representation and reconstruction of signals, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of shift-invariant subspaces is a topic in applied mathematics and engineering, which is covered by the sub-category of signal and image processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the design of energy-efficient sampling devices, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NE).
